runs.comm: good start from Tait, short and zippy, Bell stands on his toes to defend in a hurry
oh no, don't bowl there. Short and wide at any pace gets a bowler into trouble. Bell rocks back and stylishly cuts past point for four
good comeback, fuller and faster. Bell was stuck in the crease as he steered a block to point
swing on the ball! Late from a full length, swing of the bat as well though as Bell unfurled his picture-perfect cover drive, threading through the infield for another boundary
Bell tip-toes down the wicket and aims a whoosh outside off stump. Doesn't connect
slower ball from Tait, there might need to be a few more of them. Bell sees it early and flicks it away through midwicket for three
starts full around off stump and Bell pings a Watson-esque drive straight to mid-off
Lee straight into 90mph and a single worked to a big gap at midwicket gives Davies the strike for the first time
Lee hits a decent length and line outside off stump and Davies stands still to prod to point

shorter this time, doesn't want to give Davies anything to drive. For those of you who haven't seen Davies he's got shades of Ganguly in his off-side shots. This is steered to point for a swiftly-taken single
Bell edges down the wicket and Lee responds by banging it in. The line is excellent though and Bell can only defend

excellent over from Lee. Really top stuff finishes with a sharp short ball that Bell hops to defend.  Lee rewards himself by following through a long way down to Bell and... winking at him. He just doesn't know how to be mean.
Davies didn't know much about this, he popped forward to find the ball rushing onto his bat and bobbling away. Bell called him through for a single
good straight line from Tait, no width for Bell to flay at. Punched without much timing to mid-on
there is some width here which Bell duly does flay at. Zipped through and climbed to Paine as Bell found fresh air
massive yelp from Tait as he delivered his sling here. Bell mistimed a leg-side nudge, which earned him a couple
short ball and Bell is in position to pull very early, didn't quite time it though as it trickled off the toe end towards midwicket
no ball which means it's free hit time. Full and angling towards the legs, Bell happily flicked for a couple more
ideal delivery for the free hit really. Full and straight and driven to mid-off. The free hit always ends as an anti-climax it seems
Lee has not offered anything for Bell to get hold of. Bell tries to manufacture some width by jumping leg side of the ball, but only manages to outside-edge to third man
very short to Davies again. They won't let him drive, so he steers a very cautious hook shot to fine leg to give Bell back the strike. Again
just about enough width, made wider with Bell skipping leg side, for Bell to scythe a drive through cover. The damp outfield means he only collects three
bouncer to Davies again. Good one too, slower ball that completely deceived Davies. But.. because of the bouncer earlier in the over it's been called a no ball. Lee is unimpressed
this has to be fuller, but the line - hugging off stump - is good and Davies can't get away
banged in short again and Davies is struggling a touch. Mistimes a pull shot that loops gently into space at square leg
back of a length, good stuff from Lee. Bell pinches the strike again by mistiming a pull shot
starts full and straight and Bell toe-ends a drive back to the bowler
Bell hops down the wicket and Watson responds by shoving it in short. Odd shot in the end. Flat-bat tennis swat that is timed well enough for Bell to pick up a couple down the ground
down the wicket again and Bell's off-side hack trickles towards cover
Watson's short ball at Davies is not sharp enough and with fine leg up Davies pulls powerfully for four
not a great shot this. Davies wafts aimlessly outside off and luckily for him, missed it
Davies is hanging back and desperate for some width outside off, doesn't get it and has to hack to leg
ooops, bad Mitch to start. Really bad. Slung six metres wide of off stump
follows up with a straighter ball that Bell murders to mid-off. Just like Watson, that.
short and sharp, Bell hurries into a pull shot that he doesn't quite get hold of
Davies just cannot get away. He gets a delivery tight on off stump and can only drop it towards cover for a well-taken single
for the first time in about a year, Bell is struggling for timing. He aims a booming drive here and it skews away past mid-off for a couple
short ball that Bell got deep into his crease and had an absolute muller at. No finesse, but strong enough hack to leg to carry it over the rope
no timing again, but skewed past point for a couple more to bring up the fifty stand
starts well and it sticks in the pitch, Davies steers to point
touch shorter and Davies gets hold of a firm pull shot that should have been four until some remarkable sliding fielding from Smith saves on the midwicket rope
fetched into the leg side for another single
Bell down the wicket and pushing this right-arm dart to long-off
Davies jumps outside leg and gives himself room to drive, airily through cover for a couple
shoved into the leg side again, dragged really. No great timing but enough to earn a couple more
Bell dances down the wicket which forces Johnson short, pulled firmly in front of midwicket for two more
Johnson strikes! Lands a straight ball, touch slower too, Bell was aiming an almighty thwack over cow corner but ended up dragging into his stumps
flicked off the hip with a snap of the wrists to get away straight away
slung full and into Davies' pads, he clips neatly away to deep midwicket
Cheers and boos ring loud as Pietersen falls! Johnson dished up a full drive-me ball that Pietersen climbed into, only to pick out White at cover who held an excellent low catch
Collingwood pushes his first ball wide of cover to get him off the mark. Just needs to steady England for a few overs
starts by tossing one up towards the pads, Collingwood is the master of nurdle and it gets him two to midwicket
enough width for Collingwood to clunk an inelegant drive to deep point
ah, lovely shot. Ganguly-esque again from Davies as he clears his front leg to a left-arm spinner and eases a swing to wide long-on for four
tries to repeat the shot, but without any of the timing so it only earns a single
beaten outside off stump! Spin for O'Keefe
this time Collingwood uses his feet, shuffling down to push a single to long-off
good start to the new spell, back of a length around off stump, Collingwood pushes firmly to cover
shortish again and Collingwood steers to point. Two dots
Watson joining the dots and building pressure here. Collingwood struggling to find his range
finally he gets off strike, poking a single towards mid-on
Davies flicks to leg in search of two, but square leg races in from the boundary to keep it to one

Collingwood's difficult run continues. Watson aimed full and Collingwood tried to clear mid-off with a drive. The timing is not there though and it goes gently to mid-off who jumps to take the chance above his head
drive his first ball firmly to short-cover who fumbles and allows a single
Davies aims a drive as well, without quite timing it, wide of cover
very correct forward defence here. Good work from Hussey
Morgan earns himself a single courtesy of an off-drive
good over this, Davies whips a single towards midwicket
the middle overs proving difficult for England, just as they did for Australia. Morgan only managing a single wide of mid-off
good work from Watson, hitting a length and line and Morgan very respectful in defence
Morgan remains pinned to the crease in defence
after seeing a couple Morgan is happy to drill a drive back at the bowler, some very smart fielding from Warner at mid-on saves a boundary
Davies, who has hardly had any strike, wanders over to the off side and whips a single into the square-leg region
just short enough for Watson to chop down to third man but it's still just a single
good slower ball deceives Davies who gave himself room to cut, but couldn't wait on it long enough. Just three from the over and Australia are right in this
touch of width but Morgan's cut finds point
valuable, pressure-easing boundary. Johnson misses his line and it's nudged down to the fine leg boundary
back on it now from Johnson and Morgan has to hurry to defend
back of a length here and Morgan can only stand up on his toes to defend
shout of catch and Morgan flicks uppishly through midwicket
Davies hanging deep in his crease and wheels away a pull shot, without timing it particularly well
game on now! Davies gone this time, his final mistimed shot of the innings. Hanging back and driving to try and clear mid-off but Warner dives forward to take the chance
he stays on 0, pushing gently to mid-off
dot ball again, Wright defending from the crease
no duck this time for Wright, steers a single wide of point
push and go from Morgan. Dropping this from under his eyes for a single to cover
another pinched single. Dropped towards mid-on and Wright hares off down the other end. Excellent work from Watson again
Hussey starts well outside off stump and Wright flashes a drive to deep point
quicker ball here and Morgan misses an attempted nurdle, bobbles past the keeper for a single
Wright clips to leg and scampers two to the deep-set field
flashed drive, he has very quick hands, to a tossed up delivery around off stump
Hussey lucky here, dragged down a short ball but Morgan's pull shot picked out fine leg
beaten outside off stump to finish the over
bit of width first up and Morgan's chops without much timing to point
ooh, nervy times for Morgan. Aims a big pull shot but gets a toe-end that loops straight for a single
Wright again cuts, bat and arms a whirr, scampers a couple
banged in short and Wright aims a big hook shot, eyes off the ball, no timing and it bobbles to fine leg
21 balls since the last boundary as Morgan's cut shot finds deep point
Wright gives himself some room to drive but it only gets a single. Australia have managed these middle overs superbly
Wright aims a big leg-side slug, needless to say there isn't much timing, but he clears midwicket and hares back for two
flash and four! Wright didn't know much about it but he won't mind. Skipped down the wicket and outside leg, flew off the edge past the keeper for four
Tait aims down the leg side and Wright thinks he flick has four, it doesn't thanks to some excellent fielding on the rope
Big shot doesn't come off! Wright tries to clear mid-off but Steve Smith times his jump perfectly to take the catch above his head
very sharp and a good line from Tait, Bresnan stays leg side of the ball to poke a single
swing and a miss outside off stump! Morgan hasn't found his range and that's why England are struggling. Australia in the box seat now!

chaos! Which only earns a single after all that. Bresnan smacked a drive to mid-off. Morgan had set off for a single but Bresnan didn't move. The throw came in, missed the stumps and ran away for an over throw
that's the match! Morgan has gone! Got a leg-stump half-volley and tried to heave it over deep midwicket, really struck it well but the MCG is a big ground and he couldn't clear the fielder
fullish ball clunked down the ground but just for a single
excellent slower ball sees Woakes aim a drive over extra cover, only for it to loop towards mid-on
slower-ball bouncer that Bresnan heaves to leg for a couple. England need more than that
repeat delivery and a repeat shot. Johnson finishes a good spell - the three biggest wickets
England need boundaries but this is angled to third man for just a single
top work from Tait. Full and tailing in, crashes into the lads as Bresnan aimed an optimistic hack
yorker again, nothing Woakes can do with that. Pushed gently to mid-off
Tait is doing a fine job here. Landing every yorker and Bresnan can do nothing but bottom-edge to fine leg for a single
and again! Big smile from Tait, he knows he's right on top of things here. Yorker lands perfectly
not smiling this time! After five perfect yorkers this is fired full and way, way down the leg side for five wides
Bresnan gives himself room, England needed a boundary this delivery but instead it's slugged out to deep cover
good start from Lee, low full toss that Bresnan slugs to long-off. Two more but boundaries needed
slower ball, touch shorter too, and Bresnan can't find the boundary. Shoving it to leg
just a single this time. The crowd roar, Australia nearly home now! Lee is full and fast and finds an inside edge
how about that! Can Woakes be a hero again!? Madness. England have barely timed a ball all innings but Woakes got deep into his crease and smashed this miles over long-on into the stands
back of a length and Woakes can't time his pull shot. They needed two but couldn't come back for a second
Australia have broke their duck! That's the game! England's run of eight straight Twenty20 wins comes to an end as Bresnan's hoik only trickles away for one.
